This paper deals with natural language processing and word sense disambiguation, which are topics covered in the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the impact of genre and topic variations on word sense disambiguation, which could fall under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
